  "source": "[\\axiom.of.specification]\nAxiom: \"Axiom of Specification\"\ngiven: A is \\set\nthen:\n. exists: B \\:subset:/ A\nDocumented:\n. description: \"If $A$ is a set and $P(x)$ is a formula of first order logic, then there exists a set $B = \\{x \\in A \\mid P(x)\\}$ containing precisely each $x \\in A$ such that $P(x)$ is true. The set $B$ is unique by the axiom of extension.\"\nId: \"1a505620-e0b9-42a8-955a-9480abb85a3e\"",
